Note: This repository also contains hardware design files (CAD models, PCB
designs in /hardware) alongside software and documentation. MIT is applied
project-wide here for simplicity, common practice for personal/portfolio
repos, and maximum compatibility with how most people reuse small project
files. If this project grows into something with external hardware
contributors or a real open-hardware community around it, consider
re-licensing the /hardware directory specifically under CERN-OHL-S-2.0,
which is purpose-built for open hardware (see README licensing note).
